# BRC info page label
msgid "About BRC"
msgstr "Ka ñi zungu peyum kom mapu BRC"

# BRC info page content
msgid ""
"The <1>Biological Records Centre</1> (BRC), established in 1964, is a "
"national focus in the UK for terrestrial and freshwater species recording. "
"BRC works closely with the voluntary recording community, principally "
"through support of national recording schemes and societies. BRC is "
"supported by the Joint Nature Conservation Committee (JNCC) and the Centre "
"for Ecology & Hydrology (UKCEH). The work of BRC is a major BRC of the "
"National Biodiversity Network (NBN)."
msgstr ""
"TI <1> Mongelechi trawün </1> ( BRC)  wirrintukungelu 1964 tripantü mew, "
"kiñe trawupeyüm kom zungu mew mapu kulliñ ka ko kullin. EL BRC rume "
"kellukeingün ti pu lof mew küme zum kechi, zoy kellukeingün tañi küme "
"tripayayel kom pule. EL BRC zoy kelluntukuniey kom engun tañi kumelkaleael "
"ka warzaleael kom mapu (JNCC) ka ti trawun mongelelu ka nielu ko (UKCEH) ka "
"ti küzaw BRC zoy ngünenielu BRC Ti kom trapün nielu itro fill mongen (NBN) ."

# BRC info page content
msgid "Which app should I use?"
msgstr "¿Chem wirrin zuamaimi?"

# BRC info page content
msgid ""
"You might have noticed that several of<1> BRC apps</1> feature some of the "
"same species? We have introduced the BRC Approved logo to signify that data "
"from our apps all go to the same place. Therefore, you are free to choose "
"which app you use to record a given species. All records will be sent to the"
" same place, treated in the same way and will meet the established standards"
" required by the Biological Record Centre."
msgstr ""
"¿Pelu trokiwülmi kom tüfachi zungu<1> BRC app</1> kom chem trokifilmy  kom "
"chem kun?  tukufillin tati pelon llüfken BRC tayin fey piam kom ti zungu "
"amuley ti tüfachi zungu mew . eymi tami pin mew kizu zulli eymi chem zungu "
"mi küzawael tami wirrin tukuael kumeke zungu . kom wirrin werkungeay kiñe "
"püle mütem, kom ti pu wirrin werkungey  kiñe pule müten kom femngechi "
"lowngeay ka femayngün kom kümelkaleu mew ti itro fill mongen pezi kelu."

